# =============================================================================
# OPTION 1: Auto-Refreshing OAuth (Recommended for Production)
# =============================================================================
# This provides automatic token refresh - tokens never expire!
#
# Setup Instructions:
# 1. Go to https://console.cloud.google.com/apis/credentials
# 2. Create a new OAuth 2.0 Client ID (or use existing)
# 3. Add authorized redirect URI: http://localhost:3000/api/auth/callback
# 4. Copy Client ID and Client Secret
# 5. Go to https://developers.google.com/oauthplayground/
# 6. Click settings (⚙️) -> Check "Use your own OAuth credentials"
# 7. Enter your Client ID and Client Secret
# 8. In "Step 1", select "YouTube Data API v3" -> All scopes
# 9. Click "Authorize APIs" and sign in
# 10. In "Step 2", click "Exchange authorization code for tokens"
# 11. Copy the "Refresh token" (only shown once!)
#
# GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID=your_client_id.apps.googleusercontent.com
# GOOGLE_CLIENT_SECRET=your_client_secret
# GOOGLE_REFRESH_TOKEN=your_refresh_token
#
# =============================================================================
# OPTION 2: Static OAuth Token (Simple but expires in 1 hour)
# =============================================================================
# Quick setup but requires manual token refresh every hour
#
# 1. Go to https://developers.google.com/oauthplayground/
# 2. Select "YouTube Data API v3" -> All scopes
# 3. Click "Authorize APIs" and sign in
# 4. Click "Exchange authorization code for tokens"
# 5. Copy the "Access token"
#
# YOUTUBE_OAUTH_TOKEN=your_access_token_here
#
# =============================================================================
# OPTION 3: No OAuth (May encounter bot detection)
# =============================================================================
# Leave all above empty to use fallback agent (less reliable)

# Optional: Add any custom configuration here if needed in the future
# NEXT_PUBLIC_APP_URL=http://localhost:3000
